European Coal Advances for a Second Day, Trades at $126 a Ton

-- B y   Y i n g   D i a o
-- 
2011-08-11T10:23:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-11/european-coal-advances-for-a-second-day-trades-at-126-a-ton.html
European coal rose for a second day.  Thermal coal burned to generate electricity climbed 40
cents to $126.25 a metric ton by 11:07 a.m. in  London . Prices
gained 0.6 percent yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ying Diao in London at   dying6@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net . 